article.description: Marlain Veal had 21 points as Southeastern Louisiana topped Central Arkansas 75-67 on Saturday. Moses Greenwood added 20 points for the Lions.
article.headline: Veal leads SE Louisiana over Cent. Arkansas 75-67
article.linkText: Veal leads SE Louisiana over Cent. Arkansas 75-67
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Marlain Veal had 21 points as Southeastern Louisiana topped Central Arkansas 75-67 on Saturday. Moses Greenwood added 20 points for the Lions. Veal made 11 of 12 free throws. He added seven assists. Greenwood had 11 rebounds for the Lions. He also had eight turnovers. Parker Edwards had 16 points for Southeastern Louisiana (11-13, 7-4 Southland Conference), which earned its fifth consecutive road victory. Maxwell Starwood added seven rebounds. Hayden Koval had 14 points for the Bears (10-14, 5-6), who have now lost four games in a row. DeAndre Jones added 12 points. Thatch Unruh had 11 points. The Lions leveled the season series against the Bears with the win. Central Arkansas defeated Southeastern Louisiana 73-71 on Jan. 5. Southeastern Louisiana faces UIW at home on Wednesday. Central Arkansas plays Houston Baptist at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
